The more serious problem, according to experts, is, for example, the use of EU subsidies for projects that have no indication whatsoever to do with the deepening of European integration, but that have been imposed by the Member States in the budgetary negotiations.
Emotions among the Czechs also arouse that, like other countries of the Union, the Czech Republic must fight in Brussels for the right to a specific designation of its traditional products, and it will not always succeed in this match.
After six years of fighting with the Germans and the Austrians, the Czechs defended the name of Olomouc shapes, but the domestic rum, whose tradition dates back to the 19th century, had to be renamed a tuzemák by our manufacturers.
