These changes in social standards have helped to increase the number of free people and to delay marriages and the procreation of children, resulting in a reduction in the birth rate in Singapore.
While there were efforts under immigration policy to drastically increase the influx of immigrants as a measure against the decline in population, this caused displeasure among local people.
