The government is trying not to build so many small houses.
For example, it started to affect real estate business.
The City Development Office began to regulate the number of small flats known as "shoeboxes," which can be built in certain urban areas.
These apartments have an area of 46 square meters and had a great success in the marketability.
However, there is a concern that these apartments can promote a bachelor lifestyle and discourage developers from building large family houses.
